125/*
126 * An afio large ASCII header, which they named itself.
127 * afio utility uses this header, if a file size is larger than 2G bytes
128 * or inode/uid/gid is bigger than 65535(0xFFFF) or mtime is bigger than
129 * 0x7fffffff, which we cannot record to odc header because of its limit.
130 * If not, uses odc header.
131 */
132#define afiol_magic_offset 0
133#define afiol_magic_size 6
134#define afiol_dev_offset 6
135#define afiol_dev_size 8 /* hex */
136#define afiol_ino_offset 14
137#define afiol_ino_size 16 /* hex */
138#define afiol_ino_m_offset 30 /* 'm' */
139#define afiol_mode_offset 31
140#define afiol_mode_size 6 /* oct */
141#define afiol_uid_offset 37
142#define afiol_uid_size 8 /* hex */
143#define afiol_gid_offset 45
144#define afiol_gid_size 8 /* hex */
145#define afiol_nlink_offset 53
146#define afiol_nlink_size 8 /* hex */
147#define afiol_rdev_offset 61
148#define afiol_rdev_size 8 /* hex */
149#define afiol_mtime_offset 69
150#define afiol_mtime_size 16 /* hex */
151#define afiol_mtime_n_offset 85 /* 'n' */
152#define afiol_namesize_offset 86
153#define afiol_namesize_size 4 /* hex */
154#define afiol_flag_offset 90
155#define afiol_flag_size 4 /* hex */
156#define afiol_xsize_offset 94
157#define afiol_xsize_size 4 /* hex */
158#define afiol_xsize_s_offset 98 /* 's' */
159#define afiol_filesize_offset 99
160#define afiol_filesize_size 16 /* hex */
161#define afiol_filesize_c_offset 115 /* ':' */
162#define afiol_header_size 116

174#define CPIO_MAGIC 0x13141516
175struct cpio {
176 int magic;
177 int (*read_header)(struct archive_read *, struct cpio *,
178 struct archive_entry *, size_t *, size_t *);
179 struct links_entry *links_head;
180 int64_t entry_bytes_remaining;
181 int64_t entry_bytes_unconsumed;
182 int64_t entry_offset;
183 int64_t entry_padding;
184
185 struct archive_string_conv *opt_sconv;
186 struct archive_string_conv *sconv_default;
187 int init_default_conversion;
188};

220int
221archive_read_support_format_cpio(struct archive *_a)
222{
223 struct archive_read *a = (struct archive_read *)_a;
224 struct cpio *cpio;
225 int r;
226
227 archive_check_magic(_a, ARCHIVE_READ_MAGIC,
228 ARCHIVE_STATE_NEW, "archive_read_support_format_cpio");
229
230 cpio = (struct cpio *)calloc(1, sizeof(*cpio));
231 if (cpio == NULL) {
232 archive_set_error(&a->archive, ENOMEM, "Can't allocate cpio data");
233 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);
234 }
235 cpio->magic = CPIO_MAGIC;
236
237 r = __archive_read_register_format(a,
238 cpio,
239 "cpio",
240 archive_read_format_cpio_bid,
241 archive_read_format_cpio_options,
242 archive_read_format_cpio_read_header,
243 archive_read_format_cpio_read_data,
244 archive_read_format_cpio_skip,
245 NULL,
246 archive_read_format_cpio_cleanup,
247 NULL,
248 NULL);
249
250 if (r != ARCHIVE_OK)
251 free(cpio);
252 return (ARCHIVE_OK);
253}

256static int
257archive_read_format_cpio_bid(struct archive_read *a, int best_bid)
258{
259 const unsigned char *p;
260 struct cpio *cpio;
261 int bid;
262
263 (void)best_bid; /* UNUSED */
264
265 cpio = (struct cpio *)(a->format->data);
266
267 if ((p = __archive_read_ahead(a, 6, NULL)) == NULL)
268 return (-1);
269
270 bid = 0;
271 if (memcmp(p, "070707", 6) == 0) {
272 /* ASCII cpio archive (odc, POSIX.1) */
273 cpio->read_header = header_odc;
274 bid += 48;
275 /*
276 * XXX TODO: More verification; Could check that only octal
277 * digits appear in appropriate header locations. XXX
278 */
279 } else if (memcmp(p, "070727", 6) == 0) {
280 /* afio large ASCII cpio archive */
281 cpio->read_header = header_odc;
282 bid += 48;
283 /*
284 * XXX TODO: More verification; Could check that almost hex
285 * digits appear in appropriate header locations. XXX
286 */
287 } else if (memcmp(p, "070701", 6) == 0) {
288 /* ASCII cpio archive (SVR4 without CRC) */
289 cpio->read_header = header_newc;
290 bid += 48;
291 /*
292 * XXX TODO: More verification; Could check that only hex
293 * digits appear in appropriate header locations. XXX
294 */
295 } else if (memcmp(p, "070702", 6) == 0) {
296 /* ASCII cpio archive (SVR4 with CRC) */
297 /* XXX TODO: Flag that we should check the CRC. XXX */
298 cpio->read_header = header_newc;
299 bid += 48;
300 /*
301 * XXX TODO: More verification; Could check that only hex
302 * digits appear in appropriate header locations. XXX
303 */
304 } else if (p[0] * 256 + p[1] == 070707) {
305 /* big-endian binary cpio archives */
306 cpio->read_header = header_bin_be;
307 bid += 16;
308 /* Is more verification possible here? */
309 } else if (p[0] + p[1] * 256 == 070707) {
310 /* little-endian binary cpio archives */
311 cpio->read_header = header_bin_le;
312 bid += 16;
313 /* Is more verification possible here? */
314 } else
315 return (ARCHIVE_WARN);
316
317 return (bid);
318}
319
320static int
321archive_read_format_cpio_options(struct archive_read *a,
322 const char *key, const char *val)
323{
324 struct cpio *cpio;
325 int ret = ARCHIVE_FAILED;
326
327 cpio = (struct cpio *)(a->format->data);
328 if (strcmp(key, "compat-2x") == 0) {
329 /* Handle filenames as libarchive 2.x */
330 cpio->init_default_conversion = (val != NULL)?1:0;
331 return (ARCHIVE_OK);
332 } else if (strcmp(key, "hdrcharset") == 0) {
333 if (val == NULL || val[0] == 0)
334 archive_set_error(&a->archive, ARCHIVE_ERRNO_MISC,
335 "cpio: hdrcharset option needs a character-set name");
336 else {
337 cpio->opt_sconv =
338 archive_string_conversion_from_charset(
339 &a->archive, val, 0);
340 if (cpio->opt_sconv != NULL)
341 ret = ARCHIVE_OK;
342 else
343 ret = ARCHIVE_FATAL;
344 }
345 return (ret);
346 }
347
348 /* Note: The "warn" return is just to inform the options
349 * supervisor that we didn't handle it. It will generate
350 * a suitable error if no one used this option. */
351 return (ARCHIVE_WARN);
352}
353
354static int
355archive_read_format_cpio_read_header(struct archive_read *a,
356 struct archive_entry *entry)
357{
358 struct cpio *cpio;
359 const void *h, *hl;
360 struct archive_string_conv *sconv;
361 size_t namelength;
362 size_t name_pad;
363 int r;
364
365 cpio = (struct cpio *)(a->format->data);
366 sconv = cpio->opt_sconv;
367 if (sconv == NULL) {
368 if (!cpio->init_default_conversion) {
369 cpio->sconv_default =
370 archive_string_default_conversion_for_read(
371 &(a->archive));
372 cpio->init_default_conversion = 1;
373 }
374 sconv = cpio->sconv_default;
375 }
376
377 r = (cpio->read_header(a, cpio, entry, &namelength, &name_pad));
378
379 if (r < ARCHIVE_WARN)
380 return (r);
381
382 /* Read name from buffer. */
383 h = __archive_read_ahead(a, namelength + name_pad, NULL);
384 if (h == NULL)
385 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);
386 if (archive_entry_copy_pathname_l(entry,
387 (const char *)h, namelength, sconv) != 0) {
388 if (errno == ENOMEM) {
389 archive_set_error(&a->archive, ENOMEM,
390 "Can't allocate memory for Pathname");
391 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);
392 }
393 archive_set_error(&a->archive, ARCHIVE_ERRNO_FILE_FORMAT,
394 "Pathname can't be converted from %s to current locale.",
395 archive_string_conversion_charset_name(sconv));
396 r = ARCHIVE_WARN;
397 }
398 cpio->entry_offset = 0;
399
400 __archive_read_consume(a, namelength + name_pad);
401
402 /* If this is a symlink, read the link contents. */
403 if (archive_entry_filetype(entry) == AE_IFLNK) {
404 if (cpio->entry_bytes_remaining > 1024 * 1024) {
405 archive_set_error(&a->archive, ENOMEM,
406 "Rejecting malformed cpio archive: symlink contents exceed 1 megabyte");
407 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);
408 }
409 hl = __archive_read_ahead(a,
410 (size_t)cpio->entry_bytes_remaining, NULL);
411 if (hl == NULL)
412 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);
413 if (archive_entry_copy_symlink_l(entry, (const char *)hl,
414 (size_t)cpio->entry_bytes_remaining, sconv) != 0) {
415 if (errno == ENOMEM) {
416 archive_set_error(&a->archive, ENOMEM,
417 "Can't allocate memory for Linkname");
418 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);
419 }
420 archive_set_error(&a->archive,
421 ARCHIVE_ERRNO_FILE_FORMAT,
422 "Linkname can't be converted from %s to "
423 "current locale.",
424 archive_string_conversion_charset_name(sconv));
425 r = ARCHIVE_WARN;
426 }
427 __archive_read_consume(a, cpio->entry_bytes_remaining);
428 cpio->entry_bytes_remaining = 0;
429 }
430
431 /* XXX TODO: If the full mode is 0160200, then this is a Solaris
432 * ACL description for the following entry. Read this body
433 * and parse it as a Solaris-style ACL, then read the next
434 * header. XXX */
435
436 /* Compare name to "TRAILER!!!" to test for end-of-archive. */
437 if (namelength == 11 && strncmp((const char *)h, "TRAILER!!!",
438 11) == 0) {
439 /* TODO: Store file location of start of block. */
440 archive_clear_error(&a->archive);
441 return (ARCHIVE_EOF);
442 }
443
444 /* Detect and record hardlinks to previously-extracted entries. */
445 if (record_hardlink(a, cpio, entry) != ARCHIVE_OK) {
446 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);
447 }
448
449 return (r);
450}
451
452static int
453archive_read_format_cpio_read_data(struct archive_read *a,
454 const void **buff, size_t *size, int64_t *offset)
455{
456 ssize_t bytes_read;
457 struct cpio *cpio;
458
459 cpio = (struct cpio *)(a->format->data);
460
461 if (cpio->entry_bytes_unconsumed) {
462 __archive_read_consume(a, cpio->entry_bytes_unconsumed);
463 cpio->entry_bytes_unconsumed = 0;
464 }
465
466 if (cpio->entry_bytes_remaining > 0) {
467 *buff = __archive_read_ahead(a, 1, &bytes_read);
468 if (bytes_read <= 0)
469 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);
470 if (bytes_read > cpio->entry_bytes_remaining)
471 bytes_read = (ssize_t)cpio->entry_bytes_remaining;
472 *size = bytes_read;
473 cpio->entry_bytes_unconsumed = bytes_read;
474 *offset = cpio->entry_offset;
475 cpio->entry_offset += bytes_read;
476 cpio->entry_bytes_remaining -= bytes_read;
477 return (ARCHIVE_OK);
478 } else {
479 if (cpio->entry_padding !=
480 __archive_read_consume(a, cpio->entry_padding)) {
481 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);
482 }
483 cpio->entry_padding = 0;
484 *buff = NULL;
485 *size = 0;
486 *offset = cpio->entry_offset;
487 return (ARCHIVE_EOF);
488 }
489}
490
491static int
492archive_read_format_cpio_skip(struct archive_read *a)
493{
494 struct cpio *cpio = (struct cpio *)(a->format->data);
495 int64_t to_skip = cpio->entry_bytes_remaining + cpio->entry_padding +
496 cpio->entry_bytes_unconsumed;
497
498 if (to_skip != __archive_read_consume(a, to_skip)) {
499 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);
500 }
501 cpio->entry_bytes_remaining = 0;
502 cpio->entry_padding = 0;
503 cpio->entry_bytes_unconsumed = 0;
504 return (ARCHIVE_OK);
505}

507/*
508 * Skip forward to the next cpio newc header by searching for the
509 * 07070[12] string. This should be generalized and merged with
510 * find_odc_header below.
511 */
512static int
513is_hex(const char *p, size_t len)
514{
515 while (len-- > 0) {
516 if ((*p >= '0' && *p <= '9')
517 || (*p >= 'a' && *p <= 'f')
518 || (*p >= 'A' && *p <= 'F'))
519 ++p;
520 else
521 return (0);
522 }
523 return (1);
524}
525
526static int
527find_newc_header(struct archive_read *a)
528{
529 const void *h;
530 const char *p, *q;
531 size_t skip, skipped = 0;
532 ssize_t bytes;
533
534 for (;;) {
535 h = __archive_read_ahead(a, newc_header_size, &bytes);
536 if (h == NULL)
537 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);
538 p = h;
539 q = p + bytes;
540
541 /* Try the typical case first, then go into the slow search.*/
542 if (memcmp("07070", p, 5) == 0
543 && (p[5] == '1' || p[5] == '2')
544 && is_hex(p, newc_header_size))
545 return (ARCHIVE_OK);
546
547 /*
548 * Scan ahead until we find something that looks
549 * like a newc header.
550 */
551 while (p + newc_header_size <= q) {
552 switch (p[5]) {
553 case '1':
554 case '2':
555 if (memcmp("07070", p, 5) == 0
556 && is_hex(p, newc_header_size)) {
557 skip = p - (const char *)h;
558 __archive_read_consume(a, skip);
559 skipped += skip;
560 if (skipped > 0) {
561 archive_set_error(&a->archive,
562 0,
563 "Skipped %d bytes before "
564 "finding valid header",
565 (int)skipped);
566 return (ARCHIVE_WARN);
567 }
568 return (ARCHIVE_OK);
569 }
570 p += 2;
571 break;
572 case '0':
573 p++;
574 break;
575 default:
576 p += 6;
577 break;
578 }
579 }
580 skip = p - (const char *)h;
581 __archive_read_consume(a, skip);
582 skipped += skip;
583 }
584}
585
586static int
587header_newc(struct archive_read *a, struct cpio *cpio,
588 struct archive_entry *entry, size_t *namelength, size_t *name_pad)
589{
590 const void *h;
591 const char *header;
592 int r;
593
594 r = find_newc_header(a);
595 if (r < ARCHIVE_WARN)
596 return (r);
597
598 /* Read fixed-size portion of header. */
599 h = __archive_read_ahead(a, newc_header_size, NULL);
600 if (h == NULL)
601 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);
602
603 /* Parse out hex fields. */
604 header = (const char *)h;
605
606 if (memcmp(header + newc_magic_offset, "070701", 6) == 0) {
607 a->archive.archive_format = ARCHIVE_FORMAT_CPIO_SVR4_NOCRC;
608 a->archive.archive_format_name = "ASCII cpio (SVR4 with no CRC)";
609 } else if (memcmp(header + newc_magic_offset, "070702", 6) == 0) {
610 a->archive.archive_format = ARCHIVE_FORMAT_CPIO_SVR4_CRC;
611 a->archive.archive_format_name = "ASCII cpio (SVR4 with CRC)";
612 } else {
613 /* TODO: Abort here? */
614 }
615
616 archive_entry_set_devmajor(entry,
617 (dev_t)atol16(header + newc_devmajor_offset, newc_devmajor_size));
618 archive_entry_set_devminor(entry,
619 (dev_t)atol16(header + newc_devminor_offset, newc_devminor_size));
620 archive_entry_set_ino(entry, atol16(header + newc_ino_offset, newc_ino_size));
621 archive_entry_set_mode(entry,
622 (mode_t)atol16(header + newc_mode_offset, newc_mode_size));
623 archive_entry_set_uid(entry, atol16(header + newc_uid_offset, newc_uid_size));
624 archive_entry_set_gid(entry, atol16(header + newc_gid_offset, newc_gid_size));
625 archive_entry_set_nlink(entry,
626 (unsigned int)atol16(header + newc_nlink_offset, newc_nlink_size));
627 archive_entry_set_rdevmajor(entry,
628 (dev_t)atol16(header + newc_rdevmajor_offset, newc_rdevmajor_size));
629 archive_entry_set_rdevminor(entry,
630 (dev_t)atol16(header + newc_rdevminor_offset, newc_rdevminor_size));
631 archive_entry_set_mtime(entry, atol16(header + newc_mtime_offset, newc_mtime_size), 0);
632 *namelength = (size_t)atol16(header + newc_namesize_offset, newc_namesize_size);
633 /* Pad name to 2 more than a multiple of 4. */
634 *name_pad = (2 - *namelength) & 3;
635
636 /*
637 * Note: entry_bytes_remaining is at least 64 bits and
638 * therefore guaranteed to be big enough for a 33-bit file
639 * size.
640 */
641 cpio->entry_bytes_remaining =
642 atol16(header + newc_filesize_offset, newc_filesize_size);
643 archive_entry_set_size(entry, cpio->entry_bytes_remaining);
644 /* Pad file contents to a multiple of 4. */
645 cpio->entry_padding = 3 & -cpio->entry_bytes_remaining;
646 __archive_read_consume(a, newc_header_size);
647 return (r);
648}
649
650/*
651 * Skip forward to the next cpio odc header by searching for the
652 * 070707 string. This is a hand-optimized search that could
653 * probably be easily generalized to handle all character-based
654 * cpio variants.
655 */
656static int
657is_octal(const char *p, size_t len)
658{
659 while (len-- > 0) {
660 if (*p < '0' || *p > '7')
661 return (0);
662 ++p;
663 }
664 return (1);
665}
666
667static int
668is_afio_large(const char *h, size_t len)
669{
670 if (len < afiol_header_size)
671 return (0);
672 if (h[afiol_ino_m_offset] != 'm'
673 || h[afiol_mtime_n_offset] != 'n'
674 || h[afiol_xsize_s_offset] != 's'
675 || h[afiol_filesize_c_offset] != ':')
676 return (0);
677 if (!is_hex(h + afiol_dev_offset, afiol_ino_m_offset - afiol_dev_offset))
678 return (0);
679 if (!is_hex(h + afiol_mode_offset, afiol_mtime_n_offset - afiol_mode_offset))
680 return (0);
681 if (!is_hex(h + afiol_namesize_offset, afiol_xsize_s_offset - afiol_namesize_offset))
682 return (0);
683 if (!is_hex(h + afiol_filesize_offset, afiol_filesize_size))
684 return (0);
685 return (1);
686}
687
688static int
689find_odc_header(struct archive_read *a)
690{
691 const void *h;
692 const char *p, *q;
693 size_t skip, skipped = 0;
694 ssize_t bytes;
695
696 for (;;) {
697 h = __archive_read_ahead(a, odc_header_size, &bytes);
698 if (h == NULL)
699 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);
700 p = h;
701 q = p + bytes;
702
703 /* Try the typical case first, then go into the slow search.*/
704 if (memcmp("070707", p, 6) == 0 && is_octal(p, odc_header_size))
705 return (ARCHIVE_OK);
706 if (memcmp("070727", p, 6) == 0 && is_afio_large(p, bytes)) {
707 a->archive.archive_format = ARCHIVE_FORMAT_CPIO_AFIO_LARGE;
708 return (ARCHIVE_OK);
709 }
710
711 /*
712 * Scan ahead until we find something that looks
713 * like an odc header.
714 */
715 while (p + odc_header_size <= q) {
716 switch (p[5]) {
717 case '7':
718 if ((memcmp("070707", p, 6) == 0
719 && is_octal(p, odc_header_size))
720 || (memcmp("070727", p, 6) == 0
721 && is_afio_large(p, q - p))) {
722 skip = p - (const char *)h;
723 __archive_read_consume(a, skip);
724 skipped += skip;
725 if (p[4] == '2')
726 a->archive.archive_format =
727 ARCHIVE_FORMAT_CPIO_AFIO_LARGE;
728 if (skipped > 0) {
729 archive_set_error(&a->archive,
730 0,
731 "Skipped %d bytes before "
732 "finding valid header",
733 (int)skipped);
734 return (ARCHIVE_WARN);
735 }
736 return (ARCHIVE_OK);
737 }
738 p += 2;
739 break;
740 case '0':
741 p++;
742 break;
743 default:
744 p += 6;
745 break;
746 }
747 }
748 skip = p - (const char *)h;
749 __archive_read_consume(a, skip);
750 skipped += skip;
751 }
752}
753
754static int
755header_odc(struct archive_read *a, struct cpio *cpio,
756 struct archive_entry *entry, size_t *namelength, size_t *name_pad)
757{
758 const void *h;
759 int r;
760 const char *header;
761
762 a->archive.archive_format = ARCHIVE_FORMAT_CPIO_POSIX;
763 a->archive.archive_format_name = "POSIX octet-oriented cpio";
764
765 /* Find the start of the next header. */
766 r = find_odc_header(a);
767 if (r < ARCHIVE_WARN)
768 return (r);
769
770 if (a->archive.archive_format == ARCHIVE_FORMAT_CPIO_AFIO_LARGE) {
771 int r2 = (header_afiol(a, cpio, entry, namelength, name_pad));
772 if (r2 == ARCHIVE_OK)
773 return (r);
774 else
775 return (r2);
776 }
777
778 /* Read fixed-size portion of header. */
779 h = __archive_read_ahead(a, odc_header_size, NULL);
780 if (h == NULL)
781 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);
782
783 /* Parse out octal fields. */
784 header = (const char *)h;
785
786 archive_entry_set_dev(entry,
787 (dev_t)atol8(header + odc_dev_offset, odc_dev_size));
788 archive_entry_set_ino(entry, atol8(header + odc_ino_offset, odc_ino_size));
789 archive_entry_set_mode(entry,
790 (mode_t)atol8(header + odc_mode_offset, odc_mode_size));
791 archive_entry_set_uid(entry, atol8(header + odc_uid_offset, odc_uid_size));
792 archive_entry_set_gid(entry, atol8(header + odc_gid_offset, odc_gid_size));
793 archive_entry_set_nlink(entry,
794 (unsigned int)atol8(header + odc_nlink_offset, odc_nlink_size));
795 archive_entry_set_rdev(entry,
796 (dev_t)atol8(header + odc_rdev_offset, odc_rdev_size));
797 archive_entry_set_mtime(entry, atol8(header + odc_mtime_offset, odc_mtime_size), 0);
798 *namelength = (size_t)atol8(header + odc_namesize_offset, odc_namesize_size);
799 *name_pad = 0; /* No padding of filename. */
800
801 /*
802 * Note: entry_bytes_remaining is at least 64 bits and
803 * therefore guaranteed to be big enough for a 33-bit file
804 * size.
805 */
806 cpio->entry_bytes_remaining =
807 atol8(header + odc_filesize_offset, odc_filesize_size);
808 archive_entry_set_size(entry, cpio->entry_bytes_remaining);
809 cpio->entry_padding = 0;
810 __archive_read_consume(a, odc_header_size);
811 return (r);
812}
813
814/*
815 * NOTE: if a filename suffix is ".z", it is the file gziped by afio.
816 * it would be nice that we can show uncompressed file size and we can
817 * uncompressed file contents automatically, unfortunately we have nothing
818 * to get a uncompressed file size while reading each header. It means
819 * we also cannot uncompress file contents under our framework.
820 */
821static int
822header_afiol(struct archive_read *a, struct cpio *cpio,
823 struct archive_entry *entry, size_t *namelength, size_t *name_pad)
824{
825 const void *h;
826 const char *header;
827
828 a->archive.archive_format = ARCHIVE_FORMAT_CPIO_AFIO_LARGE;
829 a->archive.archive_format_name = "afio large ASCII";
830
831 /* Read fixed-size portion of header. */
832 h = __archive_read_ahead(a, afiol_header_size, NULL);
833 if (h == NULL)
834 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);
835
836 /* Parse out octal fields. */
837 header = (const char *)h;
838
839 archive_entry_set_dev(entry,
840 (dev_t)atol16(header + afiol_dev_offset, afiol_dev_size));
841 archive_entry_set_ino(entry, atol16(header + afiol_ino_offset, afiol_ino_size));
842 archive_entry_set_mode(entry,
843 (mode_t)atol8(header + afiol_mode_offset, afiol_mode_size));
844 archive_entry_set_uid(entry, atol16(header + afiol_uid_offset, afiol_uid_size));
845 archive_entry_set_gid(entry, atol16(header + afiol_gid_offset, afiol_gid_size));
846 archive_entry_set_nlink(entry,
847 (unsigned int)atol16(header + afiol_nlink_offset, afiol_nlink_size));
848 archive_entry_set_rdev(entry,
849 (dev_t)atol16(header + afiol_rdev_offset, afiol_rdev_size));
850 archive_entry_set_mtime(entry, atol16(header + afiol_mtime_offset, afiol_mtime_size), 0);
851 *namelength = (size_t)atol16(header + afiol_namesize_offset, afiol_namesize_size);
852 *name_pad = 0; /* No padding of filename. */
853
854 cpio->entry_bytes_remaining =
855 atol16(header + afiol_filesize_offset, afiol_filesize_size);
856 archive_entry_set_size(entry, cpio->entry_bytes_remaining);
857 cpio->entry_padding = 0;
858 __archive_read_consume(a, afiol_header_size);
859 return (ARCHIVE_OK);
860}

863static int
864header_bin_le(struct archive_read *a, struct cpio *cpio,
865 struct archive_entry *entry, size_t *namelength, size_t *name_pad)
866{
867 const void *h;
868 const unsigned char *header;
869
870 a->archive.archive_format = ARCHIVE_FORMAT_CPIO_BIN_LE;
871 a->archive.archive_format_name = "cpio (little-endian binary)";
872
873 /* Read fixed-size portion of header. */
874 h = __archive_read_ahead(a, bin_header_size, NULL);
875 if (h == NULL) {
876 archive_set_error(&a->archive, 0,
877 "End of file trying to read next cpio header");
878 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);
879 }
880
881 /* Parse out binary fields. */
882 header = (const unsigned char *)h;
883
884 archive_entry_set_dev(entry, header[bin_dev_offset] + header[bin_dev_offset + 1] * 256);
885 archive_entry_set_ino(entry, header[bin_ino_offset] + header[bin_ino_offset + 1] * 256);
886 archive_entry_set_mode(entry, header[bin_mode_offset] + header[bin_mode_offset + 1] * 256);
887 archive_entry_set_uid(entry, header[bin_uid_offset] + header[bin_uid_offset + 1] * 256);
888 archive_entry_set_gid(entry, header[bin_gid_offset] + header[bin_gid_offset + 1] * 256);
889 archive_entry_set_nlink(entry, header[bin_nlink_offset] + header[bin_nlink_offset + 1] * 256);
890 archive_entry_set_rdev(entry, header[bin_rdev_offset] + header[bin_rdev_offset + 1] * 256);
891 archive_entry_set_mtime(entry, le4(header + bin_mtime_offset), 0);
892 *namelength = header[bin_namesize_offset] + header[bin_namesize_offset + 1] * 256;
893 *name_pad = *namelength & 1; /* Pad to even. */
894
895 cpio->entry_bytes_remaining = le4(header + bin_filesize_offset);
896 archive_entry_set_size(entry, cpio->entry_bytes_remaining);
897 cpio->entry_padding = cpio->entry_bytes_remaining & 1; /* Pad to even. */
898 __archive_read_consume(a, bin_header_size);
899 return (ARCHIVE_OK);
900}

902static int
903header_bin_be(struct archive_read *a, struct cpio *cpio,
904 struct archive_entry *entry, size_t *namelength, size_t *name_pad)
905{
906 const void *h;
907 const unsigned char *header;
908
909 a->archive.archive_format = ARCHIVE_FORMAT_CPIO_BIN_BE;
910 a->archive.archive_format_name = "cpio (big-endian binary)";
911

917 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);

924 archive_entry_set_ino(entry, header[bin_ino_offset] * 256 + header[bin_ino_offset + 1]);
925 archive_entry_set_mode(entry, header[bin_mode_offset] * 256 + header[bin_mode_offset + 1]);
926 archive_entry_set_uid(entry, header[bin_uid_offset] * 256 + header[bin_uid_offset + 1]);
927 archive_entry_set_gid(entry, header[bin_gid_offset] * 256 + header[bin_gid_offset + 1]);
928 archive_entry_set_nlink(entry, header[bin_nlink_offset] * 256 + header[bin_nlink_offset + 1]);
929 archive_entry_set_rdev(entry, header[bin_rdev_offset] * 256 + header[bin_rdev_offset + 1]);
930 archive_entry_set_mtime(entry, be4(header + bin_mtime_offset), 0);
931 *namelength = header[bin_namesize_offset] * 256 + header[bin_namesize_offset + 1];
932 *name_pad = *namelength & 1; /* Pad to even. */
933
934 cpio->entry_bytes_remaining = be4(header + bin_filesize_offset);
935 archive_entry_set_size(entry, cpio->entry_bytes_remaining);
936 cpio->entry_padding = cpio->entry_bytes_remaining & 1; /* Pad to even. */
937 __archive_read_consume(a, bin_header_size);

941static int
942archive_read_format_cpio_cleanup(struct archive_read *a)
943{
944 struct cpio *cpio;
945
946 cpio = (struct cpio *)(a->format->data);
947 /* Free inode->name map */
948 while (cpio->links_head != NULL) {
949 struct links_entry *lp = cpio->links_head->next;
950
951 if (cpio->links_head->name)
952 free(cpio->links_head->name);
953 free(cpio->links_head);
954 cpio->links_head = lp;
955 }
956 free(cpio);
957 (a->format->data) = NULL;
958 return (ARCHIVE_OK);
959}

961static int64_t
962le4(const unsigned char *p)
963{
964 return ((p[0] << 16) + (((int64_t)p[1]) << 24) + (p[2] << 0) + (p[3] << 8));
965}
966
967
968static int64_t
969be4(const unsigned char *p)
970{
971 return ((((int64_t)p[0]) << 24) + (p[1] << 16) + (p[2] << 8) + (p[3]));
972}

974/*
975 * Note that this implementation does not (and should not!) obey
976 * locale settings; you cannot simply substitute strtol here, since
977 * it does obey locale.
978 */
979static int64_t
980atol8(const char *p, unsigned char_cnt)
981{
982 int64_t l;
983 int digit;
984
985 l = 0;
986 while (char_cnt-- > 0) {
987 if (*p >= '0' && *p <= '7')
988 digit = *p - '0';
989 else
990 return (l);
991 p++;
992 l <<= 3;
993 l |= digit;
994 }
995 return (l);
996}
997
998static int64_t
999atol16(const char *p, unsigned char_cnt)
1000{
1001 int64_t l;
1002 int digit;
1003
1004 l = 0;
1005 while (char_cnt-- > 0) {
1006 if (*p >= 'a' && *p <= 'f')
1007 digit = *p - 'a' + 10;
1008 else if (*p >= 'A' && *p <= 'F')
1009 digit = *p - 'A' + 10;
1010 else if (*p >= '0' && *p <= '9')
1011 digit = *p - '0';
1012 else
1013 return (l);
1014 p++;
1015 l <<= 4;
1016 l |= digit;
1017 }
1018 return (l);
1019}
1020
1021static int
1022record_hardlink(struct archive_read *a,
1023 struct cpio *cpio, struct archive_entry *entry)
1024{
1025 struct links_entry *le;
1026 dev_t dev;
1027 int64_t ino;
1028
1029 if (archive_entry_nlink(entry) <= 1)
1030 return (ARCHIVE_OK);
1031
1032 dev = archive_entry_dev(entry);
1033 ino = archive_entry_ino64(entry);
1034
1035 /*
1036 * First look in the list of multiply-linked files. If we've
1037 * already dumped it, convert this entry to a hard link entry.
1038 */
1039 for (le = cpio->links_head; le; le = le->next) {
1040 if (le->dev == dev && le->ino == ino) {
1041 archive_entry_copy_hardlink(entry, le->name);
1042
1043 if (--le->links <= 0) {
1044 if (le->previous != NULL)
1045 le->previous->next = le->next;
1046 if (le->next != NULL)
1047 le->next->previous = le->previous;
1048 if (cpio->links_head == le)
1049 cpio->links_head = le->next;
1050 free(le->name);
1051 free(le);
1052 }
1053
1054 return (ARCHIVE_OK);
1055 }
1056 }
1057
1058 le = (struct links_entry *)malloc(sizeof(struct links_entry));
1059 if (le == NULL) {
1060 archive_set_error(&a->archive,
1061 ENOMEM, "Out of memory adding file to list");
1062 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);
1063 }
1064 if (cpio->links_head != NULL)
1065 cpio->links_head->previous = le;
1066 le->next = cpio->links_head;
1067 le->previous = NULL;
1068 cpio->links_head = le;
1069 le->dev = dev;
1070 le->ino = ino;
1071 le->links = archive_entry_nlink(entry) - 1;
1072 le->name = strdup(archive_entry_pathname(entry));
1073 if (le->name == NULL) {
1074 archive_set_error(&a->archive,
1075 ENOMEM, "Out of memory adding file to list");
1076 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);
1077 }
1078
1079 return (ARCHIVE_OK);
1080}
